node.text: It’s always great to get on the road and see some of our clients farms. This is our cut of the gushers grown mixed light from @terpmansion aka the emerald kid.  Such a gorgeous property and showcase grow and mixed light that is better than most indoor. Truly perfecting his craft in the emerald triangle. He’s dropping his package line soon so keep an eye out!

node.text:
@mendocinograsslands has been in the family since the beginning of our journey as a commercial nursery. This group stays true to the roots we all came up from in the old 215 days; quality and heritage. They produce some of the best cannabis in Cali and some of the best people behind the brand. The fatso is a finicky girl not many people can make her shine like these guys. When you understand the plant and what it wants she comes out like this. Nothing but love and good ol sunshine ☀️ fatso throwing down. Repost from @mendocinograsslands
•
Fatso looking rather fatso.

Legend OG x GMO
.

node.text: We lost a real one; a true legend. Frenchy was a true artist with his hash and his love for the plant and products it created was unlike any other. I was lucky to have attended some of his workshops early on and will never forget the time being able to talk and sharing the love for this plant we both have. RIP Frenchy

node.text: To address one of our last posts on our Fatso flower hitting 40% and the flood of hate mail this is coming from @kristian.phinest one of the founders of Phinest is addressing this post. This morning I had a breeder I really respect reach out and say WTF! We had a great dialogue on how can this flower hit 40% thc. @aficionadoestates The truth of the matter no one really knows what’s possible with this flower, because we haven’t been allowed to study it and test it until recently. I remember years ago Jai and I showed people plants at the emerald cup that had gone through the tissue culture process People called us Monsanto and ridiculed us that we were trying to modify the plant but the people that understood the science knew what it could do to help the plant and the industry and now there seems to be a new tissue culture lab popping up daily it seems like. I also remember hitting 30% thc and people hating the same way now we hit 40%. Funny thing is we aren’t the only ones hitting 40% I’m seeing other companies with different cultivars and different testing labs hitting this. I also just saw a company hit 8% terps, never thought that was possible. And honestly the labs hate it, because these high testing strains trigger them to get audited to make sure they are calibrated correctly and they are passing these audits. After talking with Leo for awhile this morning we decided a couple of things. I’m going to bring him cuts of the fatso next week and let him run it and document his success with it. And give him some flower and have him test it independently from the labs he works with. I know this probably still won’t be enough but like I said no one knows the boundaries of what’s possible right now with this plant that’s the truth. But I know this the fatso is different it consistently hits high THC and also high terp levels we’ve been hitting over 4%. So hate on if you will we will be here constantly pushing the boundaries to see what’s possible ✌️

node.text: This industry has always been built off of colabs. The real OGs always work together to make things better, we have always been about this and always will be. This is some new lines from a colab with our friends @terpypapi it’s a cross of the grape pie cookies from @reallycannarado and crossed with their purple dawn which is Purple Hindu x Purple Starburst from @symbioticgenetics when one of the best concentrate makers in the game says they have something with amazing terps you get excited! Got some other lines currently being pheno hunted but for now here is some eye candy!
